text.134:

text.135:

#RapplerTalk: https://t.co/iYdTxJwnrX
text.136:
Pagdanganan: In the past years, I’ve actually tried to qualify for the US Open twice, and I never qualified. So now that I was able to get in by playing in a major and finishing in the top 10, I feel like it’s very fulfilling, kind of overwhelming.

https://t.co/iYdTxJwnrX
text.137:
Pagdanganan: The past few tournaments, I was trying to get in, I was pushing myself, but I didn’t play that great. And then it just so happened I played good in a major.

#RapplerTalk: https://t.co/iYdTxJwnrX
text.138:
Pagdanganan on qualifying for the US Women’s Open: After the round, my caddie told me, “Oh, I think you might have just qualified for the US Open.” It wasn’t until after, when I was being interviewed already, “Wow, I got into the US Open.”

#RapplerTalk: https://t.co/iYdTxJwnrX
text.139:
Pagdanganan: Sometimes I do put a little pressure on myself. My goal was to finish at least in the top 10 – I was already in it, I need to stay in there. So it was like, maybe this will help me, because I didn’t really know where I was at that point.

https://t.co/iYdTxJwnrX
text.140:
Pagdanganan: As soon as I hit the putt and my ball started rolling on the line that I had just imagined it to pass, “I think I’m going to make a birdie”... It’s better late than never, but I made one on the last hole.

#RapplerTalk: https://t.co/iYdTxJwnrX
text.141:
Pagdanganan: But then I hit my second shot, it wasn’t the shot that I was trying to execute, but I probably had like a 30 foot putt for a birdie, and I said, there’s still a chance that you can make it.

#RapplerTalk: https://t.co/iYdTxJwnrX
text.142:
Pagdanganan: I thought to myself, “You played two rounds with 10 birdies, and now you’re playing the last round and you haven’t made a single one.” On the last hole, I was like, “Just hit one good drive and a solid second shot.”

#RapplerTalk: https://t.co/iYdTxJwnrX
text.143:
Pagdanganan: I felt good about those two rounds. Usually I’m an aggressive player, but of course, you can be too aggressive. If you miss it on the wrong side, then it’ll be a little bit harder to save a par.
